post_text: Mrs. Scior and Ms. Moorman took their Ag classes outside on this beautiful day to learn forestry with the use of a tree scale stick, a useful tool for measuring trees. The stick is primarily used to measure the diameter of standing trees in inches. It can also be used to measure the diameter and estimate the volume. Great lesson!

post_text:
Congratulations to Josh Poole and Jack Latham for being selected to serve as Teen Ambassador Board Members with the Attorney General Dave Yost.

The mission of the Teen Ambassador Board is to provide Ohio’s future leaders with an inside look at Ohio law and government. The Board consists of high school students from around the state. Applicants selected will serve a one-year term and convene twice in Columbus during their tenure on the Board. Members will advise the office on issues relating to teens and work with their peers to develop solutions to those issues.

We understand that students, parents/guardians, and our community have many questions regarding the upcoming school year in these unprecedented times. We appreciate your continued support and patience as we work together to ensure that quality education continues at Westfall Local Schools in a safe and healthy manner.

Please take a moment to read through the answers to some frequently asked questions that our administration has received over the past few weeks. Please keep in mind that these protocols may need to be adjusted periodically in order to maintain compliance with local, state, and federal guidelines.

We'd like to also remind parents/guardians to complete the questionnaire at https://forms.gle/DA4Z2tVFWMkrfuJg7 sharing your intentions for the 2020-2021 school year with an extended deadline of Monday, August 10.

FREQUENTLY ASKED QUESTIONS:
https://www.westfallschools.com/article/281939?org=wlsd

Westfall Local School District
July 7 at 11:11 AM ·

Recently, an EMT squad unit in one of our district communities was dispatched to a house for an unresponsive adult female. The EMTs were told that the patient was not breathing, but CPR was in progress. When the squad arrived, a 16-year-old Westfall student was in the process of performing CPR chest compressions with the help of a sibling, working to keep the airway open. Upon initial inspection, the patient was not breathing and had no pulse. The EMTs were able to administer nasal Narcan, which brought the patient back and eventually became responsive. Thankfully, our Westfall student had performed at least 8 minutes of CPR, and the EMTs had a quick response. It's unsure what would have… More

Open enrollment applications and guidelines for the 2020-2021 school year are available on our website at http://www.westfallschools.com/Enrollment.aspx

Applications must be returned to the board office by May 15, 2020, and must include two forms of proof of residency. A separate application must be filled out for each student applying for open enrollment. At this time, please mail your application(s) with your proofs of residency to:

Westfall Local Schools
Attn: Open Enrollment
19463 Pherson Pike
Williamsport, OH 43164

Decisions on open enrollment acceptance will be made as quickly as possible after May 15, 2020, and families will be notified in a timely manner of their status for the 2020-2021 school year. If you have any questions, please email Paula Dumm at paula.dumm@westfallschools.com

We at Westfall loved to cruise the strip in Circleville back in the day, so why not do it again! Saturday night (May 2) from 6:00 pm - 10:00 pm, Jeff Coleman has organized another "Take back the strip," and along with cruising, they are doing a food drive at Herald Square (778 N. Court St.) to help Westfall CARES and the Pickaway County Cupboard. If you're planning on cruising, please consider donating!

Then on Sunday, Westfall CARES will be hosting a Food Donation Drive-Thru from 4:00 pm - 6:00 pm behind Westfall Elementary School. Items needed for the pantry:

Peanut Butter
Jelly
Canned Pasta
Canned Vegetables
Canned Fruit
Granola Bars
Cereal
Pudding/Applesauce Cups
Ramen Noodles
Fruit Snacks
Oatmeal
Chunky Soups
Juice Bottles
Individually Bagged Snacks
Pop-Tarts

So this weekend Westfall CARES has 2 food drives! One at the cruise-in Saturday night and one at the school on Sunday.

Thank you for all of your support!
GO MUSTANGS!

Westfall FFA cordially invites you to "attend" the Ohio FFA Celebration! And the best part...you can attend in your pajamas!

Monday, May 4th
4pm State Star Recognition-Brandon Fleak, a finalist in Star Placement

Wednesday, May 6th

HIGH SCHOOL STUDENTS: When the school building closed in March, many of our students had items remaining in their lockers. The following schedule is set up for students to return to the building and retrieve those items.

We ask that students only come during their assigned time to keep the groups as small as possible. Students will be asked to retrieve their items, drop any school materials which need to be returned in designated boxes, and then exit the building and grounds. Students will not be permitted to gather in the hallways or the parking lots.

Stay tuned! Elementary and Middle School schedules will be posted soon.

Our tech guys are amazing! They have been working with SOMACC (Southern Ohio Makers Against COVID Coalition), using five of Westfall's 3D printers from campus to create Prusa 3D printed face shields and face mask extenders to help local medical organizations in Southern Ohio. The SOMACC group currently has an order for 3,300 masks, with over 800 printed and delivered to 30 different medical facilities throughout Southern Ohio!

Westfall Local School District
April 8 at 3:42 PM ·

Another amazing day at Westfall! Again, we're so grateful and blessed for all of the wonderful volunteers that came out to help create, distribute, and deliver care packages today! Our numbers have grown since our last distribution! We are now serving over 130 families in the Westfall District. We're proud to partner with Westfall CARES to make sure our children are well-fed and supplied with learning opportunities while they are at home!

As a reminder, Westfall Local Schools is providing a week's worth of FREE breakfast and lunch for our Westfall students each week until the Governor gives us the all-clear to come back to school, so be sure to stop by next Tuesday to grab yours at the following locations: http://www.westfallschools.com/protected/ArticleView.aspx?iid=5PIPBB&dasi=3GGB

And, if you have recently experienced a sudden change of income due to the economic consequences of COVID-19, we encourage you to complete an application for Westfall's free and reduced meal program for your student(s). Visit the following link at https://www.myschoolapps.com/Application.

If you owe any money, an invoice has been emailed to you, so please check with your parents. If you would prefer to pay in advance over the phone, please call 1-800-Jostens. Just a reminder, cash is accepted on the delivery day, but checks are NOT for final payment. If you have questions, please call 1-800-Jostens. Congratulations, Class of 2020!

post_text: Westfall Local Schools has been working closely with Westfall CARES to assure that our students are well-fed during this crisis. Anyone who wishes to make a monetary donation toward Westfall CARES is welcome to drop it off at the Williamsport Savings Bank drive-through window, drop into the night deposit slot in the bank's door or mail to 200 South Water Street, Williamsport, Ohio 43164. Just a reminder to mark your envelope as being a donation toward Westfall CARES. Donations can also be sent virtually through PayPal using PayPal email address: shelleythomas71@yahoo.com. Your generous support is greatly appreciated by the Westfall community and the children that we serve. We are one family, coming together in a time a need. We are #mustangfamily

March 31 at 9:47 PM ·

It was a chilly day, but that didn’t keep our wonderful Westfall staff from working together to help feed our students! One parent commented via Facebook “Thank you Westfall Schools for providing Grab & Go Breakfast and Lunch! Come out and see us, social distance-style! We miss you all!

Open enrollment applications and guidelines for the 2020-2021 school year are available on our website. If your student is currently open enrolled in the 2019-2020 school year, you will be receiving your application for the 2020-2021 school year via mail this week. Applications will be accepted starting April 1st. Applications must be returned to the board office by May 15, 2020 and must include two forms of proof of residency. A separate application must be filled out for each student applying for open enrollment. At this time, please mail your application(s) with your proofs of residency to:

Westfall Local Schools
Attn: Open Enrollment
19463 Pherson Pike
Williamsport, OH 43164

Decisions on open enrollment acceptance will be made as quickly as possible after May 15, 2020 and families will be notified in a timely manner of their status for the 2020-2021 school year. If you have any questions, please email Paula Dumm at paula.dumm@westfallschools.com

post_text: What an amazing day! We're so grateful for all the wonderful volunteers from the community, Westfall CARES, Westfall School Board, Pickaway County Sheriff's Office, Westfall staff members, and PARS that came out to help create care packages for more than 67 families in the Westfall District. The goal of Westfall CARES is to make sure that no Westfall student goes hungry at home by creating weekend bags for students each week, and larger packages over the summer, and extended holiday breaks. During this time of unexpected school closure, Westfall CARES partnered with Westfall Local School District to create care packages with three weeks' worth of food that were distributed to families this afternoon by either pickup or delivery. Westfall CARES

post_text: Governor Dewine has mandated that schools close for three weeks due to the spread of Coronavirus. Due to this statement, Westfall Local Schools will be closed tomorrow, Friday, March 13th through Friday, April 3rd. All staff is to report to school tomorrow in order to prepare relevant learning activities that students can work on over the next 3 weeks. Parents and students may stop by the building tomorrow to pick up anything they may need, including medications that are routinely taken at school. All school and sport activities will be cancelled during this closure.

post_text:
High school eSports is a competitive, organized video gaming team that is a growing sensation offering students the opportunity for personal growth. Being a member of a high school eSports team develops strategic thinking, teamwork, and collaboration through popular games such as Fortnite, Overwatch, and Smash Bros.

Coached by Matthew Greenlee and Devin Schoonover, Westfall's eSports team is comprised of five teams playing three different games. Two varsity and two JV teams playing Fortnite and Overwatch, and one varsity team playing Smash Bros.

The team won their season opener two sets to one with a Fortnite match against Steubenville on Thursday, March 5th! The next match is Tuesday, March 10th where they will play Overwatch against Warren High School.

post_text:
What a day! Junior Lyndsey Daum spent Monday at Health Care Logistics job shadowing. Lyndsey was interested in the field of Business, and the HR department at HCL came up with a full-day itinerary shadowing all sorts of departments such as Purchasing and Inventory, Accounts Payable and Receivable, Marketing, Human Resources, Sales, and even Manufacturing.

When asked about her day, Lyndsey stated, "It was even better than I imagined it would be. Everyone was so nice. The finance people eased my nerves about math. I have decided that it is a career path that I'd like to pursue. I learned about many careers I didn't know existed. I had a fun time talking to them about their lives and what they do. I would highly recommend this job shadow for anyone interested in anything business-related."

Special "THANK YOU" to Health Care Logistics for being most hospitable to Lyndsey and allowing her to experience a day in the life of a Business professional.

Great job, Lyndsey! @PickawayWORKS

post_text: Sophomore Holly Baggett had a great day job shadowing at Circleville Post Acute. She was interested in the field of Nursing and decided to see what that career looks like in a nursing home facility. I love how I got to watch them do their job, and it's real-life things that I have to do when I'm in their position one day. My overall experience was amazing!" Special thanks to Circleville Post Acute for hosting our students and allowing them a sneak peek into the real world. @PickawayWORKS

post_text: Circleville is getting their very own Sheetz gas station and convenience store, and it MAY be due to the suggestions of Westfall's very own, Lyndsey Daum. Approximately 3 years ago, Lyndsey had her very first visit to a Sheetz convenience store in Altoona, PA. Lyndsey was on a mission trip to Altoona, which happens to be the birthplace of Sheetz. Lyndsey has only had one other visit to Sheetz since then, but approximately 8 months ago, she had a craving that only Sheetz could subside. So using the Instagram messaging app, she wrote to Sheetz stating her desire for a location to open in Circleville, OH. She received a message back saying they would look into it. And look into it they did… More

post_text: Senior Makayla Bryant was interested in the field of Radiology, so she spent the day job shadowing the Radiology Department at Madison Health! Job shadow experiences allow students the opportunity to explore careers, gather realistic career information, and learn workplace expectations. Makayla plans to attend Columbus State Community College and major in Medical Imaging. After this experience, Makayla stated, "I loved the job shadow. I got some good advice about degrees and programs. I asked about their working schedules. I am definitely going to school to become a Radiologist Tech! Today was a great day!" Way to go, Makayla!

post_text:
Due to the administration’s concerns for our students and community, there will be a few changes to the upcoming athletic events at Westfall High School and Westfall Middle School in regards to the recent school closings at both Zane Trace and Huntington this week due to illness.

The middle school basketball games vs. Zane Trace will not be played today, and no make-up date has been set.

The high school girls basketball games vs. Huntington for January 30th have been rescheduled to February 7th at 6:15 PM. There will not be a JV girls game that night.

Senior night for Winter Sports will be held on February 7th between the Varsity Girls and Boys basketball games vs. Huntington.

High School boys basketball games vs. Zane Trace has been postponed to Tuesday, February 4th, Freshman game will start at 4:45 PM with JV and Varsity to follow.

The Hall of Fame Dinner and Induction has been rescheduled to Saturday, February 1st vs. Paint Valley. The dinner will start at 5:00 PM, and the inductions will take place between the JV and Varsity games.

post_text:
The Westfall Athletic Department will be inducting 3 new members into the Athletic Hall of Fame on Saturday, February 1st between the JV and Varsity Boys Basketball game vs. Paint Valley.

Ginger Beard: Class of 1966 Community Member and Athletic Supporter for over 43 years

Randy Pontius: Coach and Teacher, Head Varsity Baseball Coach for 11 years, 4-time SVC Coach of the Year, 4 SVC Championships, 2-time District Runner-up. Randy also coached middle school basketball for 16 years, football for 4 years, and cross country for 6 seasons.

Kylie Goldsmith: Class of 2014, State Runner-up 100 meter dash in 2014 and 200-meter dash in 2014.

2014 State Champion Softball team, Head Coach Fred Redman, Assistant Coach Greg Rosshirt and players Kayla Tackett, Gina Rosshirt, Cassidy Williams, Denise Arledge, Kelly Fuchs, Ashley Salmons, Lauren Smith, Kelsie Robinson, Regan Stonerock, Alissa Wickline, Becca Brown, and Holley Webb.
